Relax the bun-version check in packages/script/src/index.ts so opencode
v1.15.7 builds with bun 1.3.13 from nixpkgs.

opencode's package.json pins `packageManager: "bun@1.3.14"` since
opencode#27648 (chore: Upgrade Bun one final time). The PR is a pure
metadata bump -- bun.lock + Dockerfile + storybook output -- with NO
new bun-API calls, so the runtime works identically against bun 1.3.13.

We can't ship bun 1.3.14 from nixpkgs today: PR NixOS/nixpkgs#519796
is in DRAFT because bun 1.3.14 produces segfaulting binaries when
building downstream packages (the PR's own nixpkgs-review run reports
SIGSEGVs on opencode itself, gitlab-duo, and filen-cli built with the
new bun). Until that gets resolved upstream, opencode's strict version
check is the only thing keeping kfactory pinned at opencode v1.15.4.

Bypass shape: replace the strict `^${version}` range with `>=1.3.13`
so 1.3.13 satisfies the check. Drops opencode's safety guard but the
guard is provably-conservative for the v1.15.4 -> v1.15.7 delta we
care about (read the diff: no `import { ... } from "bun"` API delta
on the opencode runtime path).

When nixpkgs ships bun 1.3.14, drop this patch and let upstream's
check pass on its own.

diff --git a/packages/script/src/index.ts b/packages/script/src/index.ts
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/packages/script/src/index.ts
+++ b/packages/script/src/index.ts
@@ -11,8 +11,12 @@ if (!expectedBunVersion) {
   throw new Error("packageManager field not found in root package.json")
 }

-// relax version requirement
-const expectedBunVersionRange = `^${expectedBunVersion}`
+// kfactory: relax to `>=1.3.13` so nixpkgs's currently-shipped bun
+// (1.3.13) satisfies the check. opencode's bun-1.3.14 bump
+// (sst/opencode#27648) was metadata-only -- no new bun-API calls in
+// the runtime path -- so the strict ^1.3.14 enforcement is conservative
+// rather than load-bearing. Drop this when nixpkgs/#519796 resolves.
+const expectedBunVersionRange = `>=1.3.13`

 if (!semver.satisfies(process.versions.bun, expectedBunVersionRange)) {
   throw new Error(`This script requires bun@${expectedBunVersionRange}, but you are using bun@${process.versions.bun}`)
